<refentry xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:scilab="http://www.scilab.org" xmlns:svg="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:ns3="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:db="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="cv_blur" xml:lang="en">
    <refnamediv>
        <refname>cv_blur</refname>
        <refpurpose>For bluring the image</refpurpose>
    </refnamediv>
    <refsynopsisdiv>
        <title>Calling Sequence</title>
        <synopsis>image_ret= cv_blur(image,ksize)</synopsis>
    </refsynopsisdiv>
    <refsection>
        <title>Arguments</title>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term>image</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Image on which blur operation needs to be applied</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            
			
            <varlistentry>
                <term>ksize</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>ksize â€“ aperture linear size; it must be odd and greater than 1</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
			<varlistentry>
                <term>image_ret</term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Blurred Image is returned to user through image_ret</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>Bluring Image</para>
        <para>This function provides the operation of blurring to the input Image, It takes the Image as a parameter and also ksize to provide customized blurring.The blurred image is given to user via "image_ret" output variable  </para>
        </refsection>
    <refsection>
        <title>Examples</title>
        <programlisting role="example">image_ret=cv_blur(original_image,3)</programlisting>

    </refsection>
